vulnerability.name: USN-6184-2
vulnerability.description: USN-6184-1 fixed a vulnerability in CUPS. This update provides the corresponding updates for Ubuntu 16.04 LTS and Ubuntu 18.04 LTS.  Original advisory details:   It was discovered that CUPS incorrectly handled certain memory operations.  An attacker could possibly use this issue to cause CUPS to crash, resulting  in a denial of service, or to possibly obtain sensitive information.

statements.status_notes: CUPS could be made to crash or expose sensitive information over the network. Available with Ubuntu Pro.
